sourceMeaningMnemonic: The <radical>jammed in</radical> radical and the <kanji>jammed in</kanji> kanji are the same!
readingMnemonic: Look down! You're <kanji>jammed in</kanji>to something. You can't move your feet. What is this?! Oh, your body's been jammed in a <reading>kay</reading>ak (<ja>かい</ja>).
readingInfo: Picture yourself jammed into a kayak. Your pants are bunching and sticking out the sides and top. You really don't fit in here.
